[2] Congo DR (North Kivu): reinforced surveillance
Date: Wed 17 Feb 2021 18:58 WAT
Source: Radio Okapi [in French, machine trans., abridged, edited]
https://www.radiookapi.net/2021/02/17/actualite/sante/ebola-biene-dr-muyembe-plaide-pour-la-multiplication-des-investigations


"We must multiply investigations to prevent the Ebola virus disease declared in the Biene health area in the Lubero territory in North Kivu from affecting the neighboring province of Ituri," declared the director of National Institute of Biomedical Research (INRB) Dr Jean-Jacques Muyembe on Tue 16 Feb 2021 to the press in Bunia while he was in transit to the neighboring province of Haut-Uele.

According to him, while citing the provincial minister of health in Ituri, one of the Ebola patients would have passed through Biakato in the territory of Mambasa, hence the need to strengthen surveillance on the Ituri side:

"Ebolavirus disease has resurfaced in North Kivu. It seems, according to our Minister of Health, one of the patients went through Biakato, which means that we have to push the investigations to find out exactly how it happened and to carry out reinforced surveillance in and around Biakato," indicated Dr Muyembe.

"The actions are already there, and we, INRB, have already sent the drugs, our MAB 114 molecule. And the WHO has already sent the vaccines. So the actions will be taken very quickly. And this surveillance does not stop only in North Kivu. It will extend even in Ituri as during the years of the epidemic from 2018 to 2020," he added.

--
Communicated by:
Mary Marshall

[The index case in the chain of transmission is becoming clearer, but the stepmother of the nurse may not be the true origin since she was misdiagnosed. Others may also have been misdiagnosed before her. And it still is not clear how she (the nurse's stepmother) became infected.

Fortunately, the country has experience and is responding quickly, giving hope for a rapid resolution once ring vaccination is in place and contacts are immunized.

As stated in earlier posts, rapid tests maintained in-country would be tremendously powerful in stopping outbreaks. - Mod.LK

